               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating it to be the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t18320405-281-victim2368" type="victimName">
                     George 
                     Tucker
                  <interp inst="t18320405-281-victim2368" type="surname" value="Tucker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-281-victim2368" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-281-victim2368" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>GEORGE TUCKER. I am <rs id="t18320405-281-viclabel1646" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-281-victim2368 t18320405-281-viclabel1646"></join> to William Clay, <rs id="t18320405-281-viclabel1647" type="occupation">saltmerchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-281-victim2366 t18320405-281-viclabel1647"></join>, of Lower Thames-street. On the 4th of March, about five o'clock, I received four 5s. papers of copper from the soup-house in Brick-lane, and put them into a bag on a board, at the top of my cart - I rode in front; the cart was empty; I observed the prisoner following the cart, and kept looking behind now and then - he must have got into the cart to take it, and in <placeName id="t18320405-281-crimeloc1648">Old-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-281-crimeloc1648" type="placeName" value="Old-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-281-crimeloc1648" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-281-off1644 t18320405-281-crimeloc1648"></join> I saw him in the cart; I came round, and called out,"Oh, you thief! you are there" - he had then got the bag of copper in his arms; he jumped out; I called Stop thief! he was stopped before I lost sight of him - he dropped the bag in the bed of the cart - I am sure he moved it from where I had placed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-281-person2369">
                  EDWARD 
                  HARDY
               <interp inst="t18320405-281-person2369" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-281-person2369" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-281-person2369" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a weaver, and live at Hoxton. I saw Tucker riding in front of his cart, and when he called out I saw the prisoner in front of the cart, with the money in his arms - he jumped out, leaving it behind.</p>

